Project description
[34m[39m
[34m[39m
[34m[39m
Colorama
Makes ANSI escape character sequences (for producing colored terminal text and
cursor positioning) work under MS Windows.
[34mPyPI for releases[39m
[34mGithub for source[39m
[34mColorama for enterprise on Tidelift[39m
[34m[39m
Installation
# or

Description
stdout
colorama.init()
ansi.sys
Demo scripts in the source code repository print some colored text using
ANSI sequences. Compare their output under Gnome-terminal‚Äôs built in ANSI
handling, versus on Windows Command-Prompt using Colorama:
These screenshots show that, on Windows, Colorama does not support ANSI ‚Äòdim
text‚Äô; it looks the same as ‚Äònormal text‚Äô.
